# Play4Cash API — Session & Auth Contract

This repo is the NestJS API. The session architecture was hardened in a multi-repo sweep
across `Play4CashPWA`, `Play4CashApi`, `Play4CashGateway`. Keep these invariants when
editing auth/guards/JWT/session code.

## JWT contract

- Signed with `JWT_SECRET`. Always include `issuer=JWT_ISSUER`, `audience=JWT_AUDIENCE`,
  `subject=userId`.
- Payload **must** carry `typ: 'access' | 'refresh'`, `jti` (UUID v4), `familyId` (UUID v4
  per login), and `role: 'admin' | 'user'`.
- Verification helpers live in `src/common/auth/jwt-token.util.ts`
  (`jwtVerifyOptions`, `isAccessTokenPayload`, `isRefreshTokenPayload`). Use them — don't
  re-implement.
- **Never set both `jti` in payload and `jwtid` in options** — `jsonwebtoken` rejects it.
  Set `jti` in payload only.

## Refresh-token reuse detection (session families)

In `src/modules/auth/auth.service.ts`:

- Every login creates a `familyId`. Redis keys (constants in
  `src/common/constants/redis-keys.constants.ts`):
  - `sessionFamilies:<familyId>` → `{ userId, currentJti }`
  - `familyRefreshes:<familyId>` (set) / `familyAccesses:<familyId>` (set) — for cascade revoke
  - `accessTokens:<token>` / `refreshTokens:<token>` — TTL allowlist
- On refresh: verify JWT → ensure family exists → ensure `payload.jti === family.currentJti`
  → ensure token still in `refreshTokens:` allowlist → rotate. **Any mismatch revokes the
  whole family** (`revokeFamily`).
- Logout revokes the whole family too (looks up `familyId` from access or refresh token).

## Guards

- **Global**: `ThrottlerGuard` → `AuthGuard`. Order matters; both wired in `app.module.ts`
  via `APP_GUARD`.
- **`AuthGuard`** (`src/common/guards/auth.guard.ts`): verifies JWT (with iss/aud), checks
  `typ === 'access'`, checks `accessTokens:<token>` in Redis, sets `req.user` and `req.token`.
  Skips routes marked `@Public()`.
- **`AdminGuard`** (`src/common/guards/admin.guard.ts`): thin — just reads `req.user.role`
  (or falls back to `ADMIN_EMAILS`). No JWT/Redis re-verification.
- **`RolesGuard`** (`src/common/guards/roles.guard.ts`) + `@Roles('admin'|'user')` decorator:
  prefer this for new code.
- **`WsAuthMiddleware`** (`src/common/guards/ws-auth.middleware.ts`): mirrors `AuthGuard` for
  Socket.IO. All WS gateways call `applyWsAuth(server, this.config, this.redis)` — not the
  raw secret.

## Roles in DB

- `User` schema (`src/modules/user/schemas/user.schema.ts`) has `role: UserRole` with default
  `user`. Login/refresh re-resolve role from DB, falling back to `ADMIN_EMAILS` allowlist
  (legacy). The signed `role` claim drives `AdminGuard`/`RolesGuard`.

## Refresh cookie

- Helpers in `src/modules/auth/auth-cookie.util.ts`. Controller (`auth.controller.ts`)
  always (a) reads refresh from `dto.refreshToken || cookie`, (b) sets the cookie on
  login/refresh, (c) clears on logout and on the public endpoint
  `POST /api/login/invalidate-browser-session`.
- `AUTH_REFRESH_COOKIE_SAMESITE=none` forces `secure: true`.

## Gateway trust

- `src/common/middleware/strip-untrusted-gateway-user.middleware.ts` strips `x-gateway-user`
  unless the request carries the `GATEWAY_INTERNAL_SECRET` on `GATEWAY_TRUST_HEADER_NAME`
  (default `x-gateway-internal`) or comes from `TRUSTED_GATEWAY_IPS`. The trust header is
  always removed before downstream handlers run.

## Rate limiting

- Global throttler in `app.module.ts` (`ThrottlerModule.forRoot`, 300/min default).
- Stricter `@Throttle` on `POST /api/login`, `/api/login/refresh`,
  `/api/login/invalidate-browser-session`, `/api/user/register`, `/api/user/verify-code`.
- `app.set('trust proxy', 1)` in `main.ts` for accurate IPs behind the Gateway.

## Tests

- Unit tests use ts-jest, no DB/Redis. See:
  `src/common/auth/jwt-token.util.spec.ts`,
  `src/modules/auth/auth-cookie.util.spec.ts`,
  `src/common/middleware/strip-untrusted-gateway-user.middleware.spec.ts`,
  `src/common/guards/roles.guard.spec.ts`,
  `src/modules/auth/auth.service.spec.ts` (in-memory Redis mock).
- Run with `--forceExit` to avoid open-handle hangs.

## Forbidden patterns

- ❌ Verifying JWTs without `jwtVerifyOptions(config)` (issuer/audience).
- ❌ Reusing `jwtid` option when payload has `jti`.
- ❌ Issuing refresh tokens without registering them under a `sessionFamilies:` entry.
- ❌ Adding `@UseGuards(AdminGuard)` to a `@Public()` route.
- ❌ Logging access/refresh token bytes (use `event=… reason=…` structured logs only).

